1
00:01:40,670 --> 00:01:45,940
[THE DEVIL BETWEEN US]

2
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,030
[Episode 2]

3
00:01:52,039 --> 00:01:53,229
Suspect: Ding Lai.

4
00:01:53,229 --> 00:01:54,070
Local of Haizhou.

5
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:55,590
Drug dealer and fraudster.

6
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:56,789
Forty-one years old.

7
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:57,950
Liu Yi.

8
00:01:57,950 --> 00:01:58,710
From Qiongyang.

9
00:01:58,710 --> 00:01:59,870
Twenty-five years old.

10
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:01,950
He came to Haizhou
with his parents in 2013.

11
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:03,210
Ding Lai's underling.

12
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:04,170
Not long ago,

13
00:02:04,350 --> 00:02:06,640
we received intelligence
from the Municipal Narcotics Unit.

14
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,840
Ding Lai, at an unknown location,

15
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:08,680
obtained a batch of

16
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,960
a new hallucinogen
from an overseas laboratory.

17
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,970
He mixed it into drinks
and snacks for sale,

18
00:02:12,970 --> 00:02:14,300
and it sold out quickly.

19
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,280
After this test run succeeded,

20
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,750
he planned to restock.

21
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,240
Three days ago,

22
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:20,190
the two of them came
from the city to Nuanfeng County.

23
00:02:20,190 --> 00:02:20,710
Most of the time,

24
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:22,640
they were under our surveillance.

25
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,680
Only around 3 p.m.
the day before yesterday

26
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:26,490
did we lose track of Ding Lai
once at Nuanhai Square—

27
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:28,090
for no more than three hours.

28
00:02:30,450 --> 00:02:31,130
Hu Wenjing.

29
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,520
Thirteen minutes before we arrived

30
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,710
at the Yuelai Hotel,

31
00:02:36,079 --> 00:02:37,470
two suspicious individuals

32
00:02:37,470 --> 00:02:38,630
left the hotel.

33
00:02:39,420 --> 00:02:42,480
It seemed a man had come
looking for someone in Room 401.

34
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:43,680
One male,

35
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,560
one female.

36
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:45,560
The male:

37
00:02:45,710 --> 00:02:47,200
about 1.78 meters tall,

38
00:02:47,230 --> 00:02:48,230
average build,

39
00:02:48,310 --> 00:02:49,120
black top,

40
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:49,710
black pants,

41
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:50,710
wearing a mask.

42
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:51,710
As for

43
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:53,079
the female:

44
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:54,190
around 1.60 meters tall,

45
00:02:54,190 --> 00:02:55,840
aged between 15 and 20,

46
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:57,190
long hair, slim build.

47
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,000
I now suspect these two

48
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,520
are associates of Lv Deli.

49
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,640
In Lv Deli's room,

50
00:03:02,830 --> 00:03:04,930
aside from a small amount of drugs,

51
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,360
we found a large quantity of laxatives.

52
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:08,840
This matches what I heard Lv Deli say
in the restaurant earlier —

53
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,840
"Give me an hour,

54
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:10,680
I'll make sure

55
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,470
she shits it out."

56
00:03:12,540 --> 00:03:13,910
So I'm almost certain

57
00:03:13,930 --> 00:03:15,810
he's using human body smuggling.

58
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:19,310
The digestive cycle of a healthy adult

59
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:21,000
is 24 to 72 hours.

60
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,800
If the drugs entered the body

61
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,120
and still hadn't been
expelled by this morning,

62
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,470
we can infer his time of entry

63
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:28,400
must not exceed 72 hours.

64
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:29,300
Jiajia,

65
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:29,930
come.

66
00:03:33,290 --> 00:03:34,730
Take this to Xiaoyu.

67
00:03:34,910 --> 00:03:38,030
Ask her to change into these
clean clothes after her bath.

68
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:39,400
So far the immigration office
has only found

69
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,960
Lv Deli's entry record.

70
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,079
The girl in the footage

71
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:43,590
has no corresponding entry record—

72
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:45,840
very likely she was smuggled in
with someone else.

73
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:46,910
We suspect this is

74
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:50,110
an organized cross-border
drug trafficking operation.

75
00:04:09,890 --> 00:04:10,730
Comrades,

76
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,750
Comrade Jin Longfeng
from the Municipal Narcotics Unit

77
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,950
was tragically killed in this mission.

78
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:18,370
We must turn our grief into strength.

79
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:19,310
From now on,

80
00:04:19,570 --> 00:04:21,620
everyone must stay on high alert.

81
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,240
Our county public security bureau

82
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:26,600
will fully cooperate with Comrade Wu Jun
of the Municipal Narcotics Unit.

83
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,870
At present, some officers

84
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:29,120
have already been deployed to hospitals

85
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,230
and major traffic routes across the city.

86
00:04:31,230 --> 00:04:33,390
We'll strive to capture Ding Lai,

87
00:04:33,550 --> 00:04:34,550
Liu Yi,

88
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,159
and Lv Deli's two accomplices

89
00:04:37,180 --> 00:04:38,310
within 24 hours.

90
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:42,390
Dad, why do you
have to cut Xiaoyu's hair?

91
00:04:45,130 --> 00:04:48,260
Because Uncle Tao's family
keeps their home very clean.

92
00:04:50,140 --> 00:04:51,070
If Xiaoyu

93
00:04:51,090 --> 00:04:52,770
is going to stay there,

94
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,610
she has to be clean too.

95
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:56,750
Right?

96
00:04:57,750 --> 00:05:00,070
Then when is Xiaoyu leaving?

97
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:06,630
In a little while.

98
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,670
Late tonight.

99
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:11,380
Can I go with you to see her off?

100
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:16,830
You are not going to sleep?

101
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:17,540
No, I'm not.

102
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:23,200
Xiaoyu, don't be scared.

103
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,720
Do you know what this is

104
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:26,470
wrapped around you?

105
00:05:27,690 --> 00:05:30,400
It's to keep your hair
from falling on you,

106
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:32,560
so you don't get dirty.

107
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:34,560
Then do you know

108
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,630
what my dad is holding?

109
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,720
It's scissors.

110
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:39,780
Snip. Snip.

111
00:05:40,460 --> 00:05:42,010
Invincible Wind Fire Wheels!

112
00:05:42,010 --> 00:05:43,110
Got you!

113
00:05:49,430 --> 00:05:50,490
Stop making noise.

114
00:05:51,510 --> 00:05:52,800
Invincible Wind Fire Wheels!

115
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,280
I told you to stop it.

116
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:56,080
Hello, Aunt Xiaoya.

117
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,100
Go sit over there.

118
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:59,880
Every time you come, you make a mess.

119
00:06:10,770 --> 00:06:11,770
Where's its head?

120
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,590
Who did this?

121
00:06:19,510 --> 00:06:20,160
Speak up!

122
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,000
What's wrong?

123
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:22,690
What happened?

124
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:25,510
Why didn't you keep an eye on them?

125
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:26,940
They've broken my stuff.

126
00:06:27,670 --> 00:06:28,730
They're just kids.

127
00:06:29,270 --> 00:06:30,490
If it's broken, just buy another one.

128
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:31,980
How am I supposed to buy one?

129
00:06:31,980 --> 00:06:33,870
That was a gift from a friend
when I was in college—

130
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:34,800
over 10 years ago.

131
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,530
Where would I even buy that now?

132
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:39,520
They're your good friend's kids.

133
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:42,280
If it weren't because I like children,

134
00:06:42,350 --> 00:06:44,680
I wouldn't be helping you look after them.

135
00:06:47,310 --> 00:06:48,370
Where's Xiaodong?

136
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:49,720
He went out.

137
00:06:55,490 --> 00:06:56,560
Listen.

138
00:06:56,950 --> 00:06:59,409
Two more groups came
today asking for money.

139
00:06:59,770 --> 00:07:01,830
Either you find a way to pay them back,

140
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,490
or you move out completely.

141
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:14,320
Honey.

142
00:07:28,350 --> 00:07:29,750
Next Monday at 10 in the morning,

143
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:31,950
let's meet at the Civil Affairs Bureau.

144
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:36,560
Do we really have to come to this?

145
00:07:37,570 --> 00:07:38,500
About the money—

146
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,950
I can help you solve it.

147
00:07:39,970 --> 00:07:40,760
I've told you,

148
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,159
it's not about the money.

149
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,880
That's just small money.

150
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,510
I can cover it with a little cash flow.

151
00:07:45,510 --> 00:07:47,159
I really can't stand this life anymore.

152
00:07:47,159 --> 00:07:47,800
I've had enough.

153
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,460
I've had enough of your mom...

154
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:51,720
And of you.

155
00:07:52,310 --> 00:07:53,950
Mom's just getting old,

156
00:07:54,130 --> 00:07:55,170
so she likes to nag.

157
00:07:55,170 --> 00:07:56,360
Then we can move out.

158
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,800
Wouldn't that solve everything?

159
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,390
This isn't about living arrangements.

160
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:00,890
Why can't you understand?

161
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,720
What problem can't be solved?

162
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,390
I'll listen to you.

163
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:04,120
I'll change.

164
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:08,270
Cheng Xiaodong,
what are you even changing?

165
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:09,510
How many times have I told you?

166
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:10,270
You don't even understand what I'm saying.

167
00:08:10,270 --> 00:08:11,070
How are you going to change?

168
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:12,560
This is how I do things.

169
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,430
Once I've made a decision,

170
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:14,120
I don't waver.

171
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:14,830
You know that too.

172
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:16,000
So stop dragging this out.

173
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,960
Pack up my things,

174
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:17,890
hand them over to me,

175
00:08:17,890 --> 00:08:19,130
and we'll be done.

176
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:20,130
Understand?

177
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:26,410
And one more thing—

178
00:08:26,410 --> 00:08:28,140
don't ever come looking for me.

179
00:08:29,290 --> 00:08:30,880
Except at the Civil Affairs Bureau,

180
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,679
I don't want to see you anywhere.

181
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,890
Hu Wenjing was on a mission.

182
00:08:46,180 --> 00:08:47,240
Why did she bring you along?

183
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:47,860
No,

184
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:49,560
Wenjing wasn't on duty today.

185
00:08:49,590 --> 00:08:50,720
Wasn't she on leave?

186
00:08:51,020 --> 00:08:54,220
The three of us planned
to go eat at Black Forest together.

187
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:56,300
When we first got to the restaurant,

188
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:58,790
Xiaoya thought a guy there
looked pretty handsome

189
00:08:58,790 --> 00:09:00,620
and wanted us to go ask for his WeChat.

190
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:01,460
But we never expected

191
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:03,680
that man turned out to be a drug dealer.

192
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:06,300
Everything went into chaos in an instant.

193
00:09:06,390 --> 00:09:07,630
During the chase,

194
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:09,510
a police officer even died.

195
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:10,440
Why did Li Xiaoya

196
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,370
insist on setting you up with a man?

197
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:15,730
And besides,

198
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,120
if something had happened to you,

199
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,380
what would I have done?

200
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:31,800
Li Xiaoya has no sense of shame herself

201
00:09:31,950 --> 00:09:33,480
and she insists on leading you astray.

202
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,800
Don't talk about Xiaoya like that.

203
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,480
I advise you to keep
your distance from her.

204
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,960
You're not the same kind of people.

205
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:45,360
I really don't know how you two
ended up hanging out together.

206
00:10:16,910 --> 00:10:17,450
Xiaodong.

207
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:17,870
You're here.

208
00:10:17,870 --> 00:10:18,670
I just finished up.

209
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:19,960
Sorry I'm late.

210
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:21,270
They're both exhausted,

211
00:10:21,270 --> 00:10:22,320
already asleep.

212
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:25,280
Why are they sleeping so deeply?

213
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,210
Where's Xiaoya?

214
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:43,340
Li Xiaoya.

215
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,200
Long time no see.

216
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:52,470
So you're the drug dealer
the police are after.

217
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:55,310
I happened to see you at the café today,

218
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:58,110
so I thought I'd come over to catch up.

219
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,240
It's done.

220
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:05,950
I've bandaged you up.

221
00:13:08,290 --> 00:13:09,490
You should leave now.

222
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:10,600
I promise—

223
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:14,010
I absolutely won't call the police.

224
00:13:19,130 --> 00:13:21,190
I remember you married an honest man.

225
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,170
How did your life become so miserable?

226
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:30,840
After all these years,

227
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,520
you're still the only woman

228
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:36,430
who can ignite passion in me.

229
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:40,080
You have that fire inside,

230
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,600
nowhere to release it,

231
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,730
so you can only use it in bed.

232
00:13:43,830 --> 00:13:44,950
Get out!

233
00:13:45,390 --> 00:13:46,250
Get out of here.

234
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:48,870
If you drive me away now,

235
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,790
I'll have no way to survive.

236
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:54,240
I don't mind

237
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:55,900
having someone accompany me

238
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,880
on the road to hell.

239
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:06,470
Li Xiaoya!

240
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,480
I know you're in there.

241
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,870
Stop playing games with me.

242
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:11,200
Debts must be paid.

243
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,150
That's only natural.

244
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,550
You can't hide forever.

245
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:14,880
Open the door right now!

246
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,330
Li Xiaoya!

247
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,990
Don't make me break it down.

248
00:14:18,010 --> 00:14:19,280
I'm telling you—

249
00:14:19,310 --> 00:14:20,690
if I don't get the money today,

250
00:14:20,690 --> 00:14:21,970
I'm not leaving.

251
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,020
I'll stay right here

252
00:14:23,020 --> 00:14:24,780
and see who can hold out longer.

253
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:31,930
How long to pick the lock?

254
00:14:31,930 --> 00:14:32,730
Five minutes.

255
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:34,390
Then hurry up and get it done.

256
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:56,430
The IOU.

257
00:15:00,940 --> 00:15:01,510
Here.

258
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:07,400
Leave now.

259
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:12,390
The money is real.

260
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:13,460
Mine's real too. Hua.

261
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:14,390
Then let's go.

262
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:29,750
Xiaoya.

263
00:15:31,150 --> 00:15:32,660
No one knows about us.

264
00:15:32,690 --> 00:15:33,690
You're safe.

265
00:15:36,350 --> 00:15:38,350
There are real feelings between us.

266
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:41,010
As long as I get through this rough patch,

267
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:45,480
I'll take back everything
that belongs to me.

268
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:46,510
When that time comes,

269
00:15:46,510 --> 00:15:47,610
I'll give you

270
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,590
everything you want.

271
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:56,520
When I first met you,

272
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:59,590
you were just a fraud
preaching success formulas.

273
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:00,480
What now?

274
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:01,740
You switched careers,

275
00:16:02,150 --> 00:16:04,550
but you're still
running the same old game?

276
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:06,700
Trying to sell me dreams again?

277
00:16:07,270 --> 00:16:08,510
Are you scared

278
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:10,020
that after you fall asleep,

279
00:16:10,020 --> 00:16:11,180
I might sell you off?

280
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,790
The money in that bag is all yours.

281
00:16:14,940 --> 00:16:17,000
There will be even more in the future.

282
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:20,010
As long as you help me this time,

283
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:23,150
I'll change the rest of your life

284
00:16:23,950 --> 00:16:26,380
and help you live the life
you've always wanted,

285
00:16:26,380 --> 00:16:28,540
just like back in Haizhou.

286
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:39,960
You'll be caught by the police
sooner or later.

287
00:16:41,830 --> 00:16:42,760
I'm not stupid.

288
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,790
I won't die with you.

289
00:16:49,380 --> 00:16:51,340
If someone keeps dealing drugs,

290
00:16:52,390 --> 00:16:54,720
there's no way they can stay free forever.

291
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,700
If you want wealth from danger,

292
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:58,300
two conditions must be met:

293
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:58,960
First—

294
00:16:59,430 --> 00:17:01,310
increase the efficiency of making money.

295
00:17:01,310 --> 00:17:02,810
You must, in the shortest time,

296
00:17:02,810 --> 00:17:04,470
earn the most money possible.

297
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:05,030
Second—

298
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:07,880
once I've earned the amount
my heart truly desires,

299
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:09,069
I'll quit for good.

300
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:11,240
This kind of risk is controllable.

301
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:12,990
When the time comes,

302
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:15,200
we'll leave Nuanhai

303
00:17:15,569 --> 00:17:17,500
and live a rich, comfortable life.

304
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:19,930
I know

305
00:17:21,569 --> 00:17:24,030
these past 2 years
haven't been easy for you.

306
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:28,540
Haven't you always
wanted to leave Haizhou—

307
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:31,720
leave this small county?

308
00:17:36,850 --> 00:17:37,720
But

309
00:17:38,340 --> 00:17:40,210
there are many ways to leave.

310
00:17:42,710 --> 00:17:44,360
The plan I designed for you—

311
00:17:45,850 --> 00:17:47,330
do you like it?

312
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:17,630
Jiajia,

313
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,480
you can't stay up all night.

314
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:21,800
Get some rest.

315
00:18:22,630 --> 00:18:23,830
I'm not sleepy.

316
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,220
Come on, move forward.

317
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:53,910
The ones behind, keep up.

318
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:01,040
All clear.

319
00:19:01,110 --> 00:19:02,130
Go.

320
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:06,480
Spot check.

321
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:07,460
Drive forward.

322
00:19:07,490 --> 00:19:08,580
Slow down.

323
00:19:09,110 --> 00:19:09,880
Come over here.

324
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:10,900
Keep moving forward.

325
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:11,660
Zhang Yan.

326
00:19:12,270 --> 00:19:13,070
Ken.

327
00:19:13,310 --> 00:19:14,280
Where are you going this late?

328
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:15,280
It's really late.

329
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:16,200
I…

330
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:19,090
I'm taking the kids
to stay at Tao's for a day.

331
00:19:20,070 --> 00:19:20,640
What happened?

332
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:21,680
Why such a big deal?

333
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:22,550
We're on a mission—

334
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:23,550
been up all night.

335
00:19:26,350 --> 00:19:26,900
Know them?

336
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:27,490
Yes.

337
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:28,320
They're my neighbors.

338
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:29,190
He used to be my mom's student.

339
00:19:29,190 --> 00:19:31,390
He's now an accountant
at the county electronics factory.

340
00:19:31,390 --> 00:19:33,030
We've known each other for years.

341
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:34,830
Why set off in the middle of the night?

342
00:19:34,830 --> 00:19:36,480
I‘m taking the kids to a friend's place.

343
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:37,270
Tao's family

344
00:19:37,270 --> 00:19:38,590
live by the seaside, right?

345
00:19:38,590 --> 00:19:40,990
I wanted to take the kids
to see the sunrise.

346
00:19:41,320 --> 00:19:42,780
Roll down the back window.

347
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:50,350
What's your relationship
to these two kids?

348
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:51,200
My daughter.

349
00:19:51,740 --> 00:19:52,620
My niece.

350
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:54,110
How old?

351
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:54,980
Nine.

352
00:19:55,610 --> 00:19:56,340
Fourteen.

353
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:58,090
Let me see your ID.

354
00:19:58,420 --> 00:19:59,150
ID.

355
00:20:01,110 --> 00:20:01,960
I left in a hurry,

356
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:02,890
didn't bring it.

357
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:03,750
Then driver's license.

358
00:20:03,750 --> 00:20:04,090
Driver's license.

359
00:20:04,090 --> 00:20:04,860
A driver's license will do?

360
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:05,420
Right.

361
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:15,980
Step out of the car.

362
00:20:16,130 --> 00:20:17,530
Open the trunk for a look.

363
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:27,820
Alright, that's fine.

364
00:20:27,820 --> 00:20:28,410
Okay.

365
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,400
Hello, officer.

366
00:20:40,630 --> 00:20:41,310
Hello.

367
00:20:42,620 --> 00:20:43,820
What's your name?

368
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,790
My name is Cheng Jiajia.

369
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:47,200
I was asking about your cousin.

370
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,310
Why isn't she talking?

371
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:50,230
Xiaoyu is sick.

372
00:20:51,030 --> 00:20:51,830
What illness?

373
00:20:52,310 --> 00:20:54,400
She has congenital intellectual issues,

374
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,860
her mind isn't very sharp.

375
00:20:56,830 --> 00:20:58,440
Has she seen a doctor?

376
00:20:58,510 --> 00:20:59,100
Yes.

377
00:20:59,130 --> 00:21:00,640
She's been seeing doctors
since she was little.

378
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:02,160
I took her to the hospital yesterday.

379
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:04,060
Yang Xinyu did her examination.

380
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:06,030
He's also my mom's student,

381
00:21:06,030 --> 00:21:07,830
a doctor at the county hospital.

382
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:09,240
Her parents are local?

383
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:09,790
Yeah.

384
00:21:09,860 --> 00:21:10,970
Call them.

385
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:15,370
It's this late—they're asleep.

386
00:21:15,370 --> 00:21:16,170
Make the call.

387
00:21:20,290 --> 00:21:21,150
I'll call them.

388
00:21:37,780 --> 00:21:39,040
You'll be a while, huh?

389
00:21:39,110 --> 00:21:40,370
Maybe the whole night.

390
00:21:45,670 --> 00:21:46,310
Connected?

391
00:21:46,310 --> 00:21:46,830
Yes.

392
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:48,710
They must be asleep.

393
00:21:48,710 --> 00:21:49,470
No answer.

394
00:21:49,860 --> 00:21:50,540
Ken.

395
00:21:51,070 --> 00:21:51,400
What's wrong?

396
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,400
Stop the car!

397
00:21:53,070 --> 00:21:53,830
Stop the car!

398
00:21:54,110 --> 00:21:55,160
Freeze—stop!

399
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,030
Stop!

400
00:21:59,450 --> 00:22:01,340
Stop the car!

401
00:22:06,810 --> 00:22:07,680
Hurry, hurry!

402
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:08,810
Don't move!

403
00:22:08,810 --> 00:22:09,550
Hands on your head!

404
00:22:09,550 --> 00:22:10,240
Hands on your head!

405
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:10,820
Get out of the car!

406
00:22:10,820 --> 00:22:11,620
Get out now!

407
00:22:12,410 --> 00:22:13,740
Out of the car, quickly!

408
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:15,880
Hands on your head!

409
00:22:17,050 --> 00:22:17,590
Get out!

410
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:18,200
Where's Ding Lai?

411
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,600
Step out for inspection.

412
00:22:23,260 --> 00:22:23,920
Get out now!

413
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:25,440
Our people blocked someone in front.

414
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:26,220
What's going on?

415
00:22:26,220 --> 00:22:27,620
Someone's been stopped.

416
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:28,760
Those behind, move up fast.

417
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:29,440
Ken.

418
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:31,350
I'll call you back in a bit.

419
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:43,950
Come.

420
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:45,120
Follow me.

421
00:23:46,030 --> 00:23:47,430
Jiajia, you stay seated.

422
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:20,950
Dad, why did you abandon Xiaoyu?

423
00:24:33,790 --> 00:24:36,400
Will Xiaoyu die?

424
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:42,830
I'm sick too.

425
00:24:42,830 --> 00:24:44,000
So one day

426
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,930
will you abandon me as well?

427
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:48,330
I didn't leave her because she's sick.

428
00:24:48,490 --> 00:24:49,890
Then why?

429
00:24:53,480 --> 00:24:54,440
She won't die.

430
00:24:55,670 --> 00:24:56,190
But…

431
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,510
This is complicated.

432
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:11,070
Xiaoyu was wearing your clothes.

433
00:26:31,540 --> 00:26:32,220
Liu Yi.

434
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:34,230
Who killed the police officer?

435
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:45,230
Ding Lai.

436
00:26:46,590 --> 00:26:47,440
He took a bullet

437
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,680
and pushed him down.

438
00:26:51,570 --> 00:26:52,960
Where was he shot?

439
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,040
In the arm.

440
00:26:54,410 --> 00:26:55,650
He said he was hit.

441
00:26:55,730 --> 00:26:57,120
I'm too exposed right now.

442
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,160
I can't run far.

443
00:26:58,310 --> 00:26:59,200
We split up.

444
00:26:59,220 --> 00:26:59,620
Okay.

445
00:26:59,650 --> 00:27:00,980
You go get the car first.

446
00:27:01,050 --> 00:27:02,780
I'll find a way out of Nuanfeng.

447
00:27:02,910 --> 00:27:03,440
Alright.

448
00:27:03,540 --> 00:27:04,060
The bag!

449
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:05,170
Give it to me.

450
00:27:13,390 --> 00:27:15,190
Who was the one trading with you?

451
00:27:15,660 --> 00:27:16,990
Ding Lai contacted him.

452
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:19,100
He said his name was

453
00:27:19,270 --> 00:27:20,310
Ao…

454
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:21,510
Ming.

455
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:22,420
Be clearer.

456
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:23,400
Ao Ming!

457
00:27:30,290 --> 00:27:31,380
Do you know Lv Deli?

458
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:32,600
No.

459
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:34,840
The one you met at Black Forest.

460
00:27:38,510 --> 00:27:39,730
That was my first time seeing him.

461
00:27:39,730 --> 00:27:40,890
I don't know his name.

462
00:27:40,890 --> 00:27:42,070
Anyway, it was arranged

463
00:27:42,070 --> 00:27:44,470
that he would carry a green canvas bag,

464
00:27:45,310 --> 00:27:46,080
and Ding Lai would wear

465
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:47,880
a black hat with a special mark.

466
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:49,240
Who set the rules?

467
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:50,400
Ao Ming.

468
00:27:50,750 --> 00:27:53,340
So is this Lv Deli actually Ao Ming?

469
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:54,960
No idea.

470
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:56,750
What was the deal about?

471
00:27:56,830 --> 00:27:58,830
Everything was decided by Ding Lai.

472
00:27:58,830 --> 00:28:00,110
You're asking me
about Ding Lai's business—

473
00:28:00,110 --> 00:28:01,240
I really don't know!

474
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:04,700
Trying to play tricks with me again?

475
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:06,450
I've told you everything

476
00:28:06,970 --> 00:28:08,420
I can say.

477
00:28:09,310 --> 00:28:10,550
What I don't know—

478
00:28:11,530 --> 00:28:13,290
shoot me and it won't help.

479
00:28:33,260 --> 00:28:37,060
[One Month Later]

480
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:52,320
Dad.

481
00:28:52,540 --> 00:28:53,540
Are you there yet?

482
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:54,120
Where?

483
00:28:54,130 --> 00:28:55,400
Where was I supposed to go?

484
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:56,850
Didn't we agree
to meet Liu's nephew at noon

485
00:28:56,850 --> 00:28:58,020
for lunch together?

486
00:28:58,240 --> 00:28:59,540
I... I forgot.

487
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:00,510
I've already started eating.

488
00:29:00,510 --> 00:29:01,940
You should apologize to them.

489
00:29:01,940 --> 00:29:02,620
Just cancel it.

490
00:29:02,620 --> 00:29:03,860
Don't.

491
00:29:04,550 --> 00:29:06,240
Liu even called me about it.

492
00:29:06,240 --> 00:29:07,350
I already promised him.

493
00:29:07,350 --> 00:29:08,630
If you stand them up,

494
00:29:08,660 --> 00:29:10,050
I'll lose face.

495
00:29:10,480 --> 00:29:11,310
Well, I...

496
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:12,700
Wenjing, you have to go.

497
00:29:12,830 --> 00:29:13,440
Madam Wenjing.

498
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,720
Alright, fine, fine.

499
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:16,000
Stop nagging. I'll go.

500
00:29:16,160 --> 00:29:16,680
Hurry up.

501
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,350
Alright.

502
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:22,680
Wenjing.

503
00:29:23,140 --> 00:29:24,520
Why didn't you go eat at the cafeteria?

504
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:25,650
I'm eating already.

505
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:27,130
You're eating already?

506
00:29:27,130 --> 00:29:28,390
I even brought you two buns.

507
00:29:28,390 --> 00:29:29,250
Hand them to me.

508
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:31,160
Watching the surveillance footage?

509
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:32,030
Nothing at all.

510
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:33,880
By the way, Director Dai said

511
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:36,000
you should go to his office right now.

512
00:29:36,460 --> 00:29:37,130
For what?

513
00:29:37,910 --> 00:29:39,170
Go and you'll find out.

514
00:29:44,230 --> 00:29:45,630
Then don't touch my food.

515
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:50,380
Eating so happily.

516
00:29:50,410 --> 00:29:52,320
My wife made it. How could it
not make me happy?

517
00:29:52,320 --> 00:29:53,450
You wanted to see me?

518
00:29:54,790 --> 00:29:55,550
Well…

519
00:29:55,650 --> 00:29:56,410
I heard

520
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:59,810
you're still reviewing
the Yuelai Hotel surveillance.

521
00:30:00,190 --> 00:30:01,830
I only do it in my spare time,

522
00:30:01,850 --> 00:30:03,410
during my own rest hours.

523
00:30:04,230 --> 00:30:04,880
Alright, alright.

524
00:30:04,880 --> 00:30:06,810
I'm not planning to criticize you.

525
00:30:07,360 --> 00:30:08,820
I called you here this time

526
00:30:09,510 --> 00:30:10,640
to let you know

527
00:30:11,270 --> 00:30:12,800
there's news from the city.

528
00:30:13,340 --> 00:30:15,200
After discussion at the meeting,

529
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:17,210
regarding Comrade Jin Longfeng's

530
00:30:17,210 --> 00:30:18,770
sacrifice,

531
00:30:19,330 --> 00:30:21,260
you bear no responsibility at all.

532
00:30:21,950 --> 00:30:23,350
They were completely fair and just.

533
00:30:23,350 --> 00:30:24,370
That's how it should be.

534
00:30:24,370 --> 00:30:25,830
Feel relieved now, right?

535
00:30:25,830 --> 00:30:28,590
But about your transfer
to the city bureau—

536
00:30:28,610 --> 00:30:30,890
it probably won't happen this year.

537
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:31,570
Why?

538
00:30:33,390 --> 00:30:34,220
Well…

539
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:36,510
Some comrades in the Narcotics Unit

540
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:38,370
have certain opinions about you.

541
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:41,350
Who could have known?

542
00:30:41,350 --> 00:30:43,430
How could anyone have known
they were in action there?

543
00:30:43,430 --> 00:30:45,800
Not pursuing
your responsibility in this matter

544
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:46,920
is already a blessing.

545
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:47,550
Right?

546
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:48,850
You're still...

547
00:30:50,070 --> 00:30:51,110
Let me tell you.

548
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:53,640
Stay away from Ding Lai's case.

549
00:30:53,820 --> 00:30:55,450
Don't glare at me.

550
00:30:55,790 --> 00:30:56,920
It's been over a month.

551
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:58,590
He's probably not
even in Nuanfeng anymore.

552
00:30:58,590 --> 00:31:00,110
Even the Municipal Narcotics Unit
has withdrawn.

553
00:31:00,110 --> 00:31:01,240
What are you fussing about?

554
00:31:01,240 --> 00:31:01,750
What do you mean I...

555
00:31:01,750 --> 00:31:02,860
Stop it.

556
00:31:03,070 --> 00:31:03,880
I say one sentence,

557
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:05,880
and you've got eight waiting for me.

558
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:07,360
I'll be honest with you.

559
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,860
I don't want you
going to the city bureau either.

560
00:31:11,510 --> 00:31:12,400
Look,

561
00:31:12,590 --> 00:31:13,480
in our bureau,

562
00:31:14,030 --> 00:31:15,800
there aren't many people left

563
00:31:15,830 --> 00:31:18,340
with ability, experience,
and the guts to fight.

564
00:31:18,340 --> 00:31:19,250
If you leave,

565
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:20,790
won't I have to train someone new?

566
00:31:20,790 --> 00:31:21,960
Don't laugh.

567
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:22,650
You really...

568
00:31:22,650 --> 00:31:24,270
You really know how to play me.

569
00:31:24,270 --> 00:31:25,240
Play you?

570
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:26,680
I'm not playing you.

571
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:28,720
I know that with your temper,

572
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:30,050
I can't stop you anyway.

573
00:31:30,620 --> 00:31:31,920
So just wait a bit more.

574
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:33,640
One year.

575
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:34,920
After this whole thing passes,

576
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:37,350
I'll personally go to the city bureau
leaders to plead for you.

577
00:31:37,350 --> 00:31:37,920
Your child is still young.

578
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:38,960
What's the rush?

579
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:39,790
My dear Director Dai,

580
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:40,920
I can't wait a year.

581
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:41,790
A whole year.

582
00:31:41,790 --> 00:31:43,200
How can I not be anxious?

583
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:44,320
My kid needs to get to

584
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,510
the primary school affiliated
with No.3 Middle School of the City first.

585
00:31:45,510 --> 00:31:47,450
Otherwise how will she
ever get into No.3 Middle School later?

586
00:31:47,450 --> 00:31:48,030
You can...

587
00:31:48,030 --> 00:31:48,640
Listen to me.

588
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:49,440
In the end,

589
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:51,960
it's all because
I didn't clear up Ding Lai's case.

590
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:53,310
How about this?

591
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:54,160
For Ding Lai's case,

592
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:55,030
I promise you,

593
00:31:55,030 --> 00:31:56,590
I will absolutely not
take up my working hours.

594
00:31:56,590 --> 00:31:57,720
I still have something this afternoon.

595
00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:58,310
After lunch,

596
00:31:58,310 --> 00:31:58,960
take a nap.

597
00:31:58,960 --> 00:31:59,480
Nap for what?

598
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:00,480
Just have a midday rest.

599
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:01,480
I'm not done talking yet.

600
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:02,350
You're done.

601
00:32:02,370 --> 00:32:02,820
I...

602
00:32:05,890 --> 00:32:08,260
[Nuanfeng County People's Hospital]

603
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:16,110
You're staring blankly.

604
00:32:16,110 --> 00:32:17,970
You didn't sleep well last night?

605
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:22,640
It's been over 2 years
bringing Jiajia for dialysis.

606
00:32:24,550 --> 00:32:26,270
Every time, the night before coming here,

607
00:32:26,270 --> 00:32:27,470
I still get insomnia.

608
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:30,410
It's almost become a routine.

609
00:32:34,150 --> 00:32:37,680
Logically, I'm someone
who adapts pretty well,

610
00:32:40,100 --> 00:32:42,560
but this is something
I can never get used to.

611
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:45,720
I know

612
00:32:47,900 --> 00:32:49,960
only the hospital can save Jiajia,

613
00:32:51,220 --> 00:32:52,700
but I just hate this place.

614
00:32:52,750 --> 00:32:53,730
I hate it so much.

615
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:58,000
And those cold, lifeless machines.

616
00:33:03,990 --> 00:33:05,590
Look how thin you've become.

617
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:07,000
You're under too much pressure.

618
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,200
Try to relax a little.

619
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:09,360
How can I relax?

620
00:33:12,590 --> 00:33:14,280
Don't you write detective novels?

621
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:15,520
What novels?

622
00:33:15,780 --> 00:33:16,840
I stopped long ago.

623
00:33:17,140 --> 00:33:18,210
No mood to write.

624
00:33:19,350 --> 00:33:21,550
And writing doesn't make money anyway.

625
00:33:22,310 --> 00:33:24,240
Now every morning when I wake up...

626
00:33:27,890 --> 00:33:30,090
There's a pile of things waiting for me.

627
00:33:30,350 --> 00:33:31,680
It never ends.

628
00:33:34,170 --> 00:33:36,700
I sometimes wish
there was something like...

629
00:33:37,550 --> 00:33:40,580
Like the systems in novels.

630
00:33:41,340 --> 00:33:42,410
Give me a task,

631
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:43,930
I complete it,

632
00:33:44,270 --> 00:33:45,070
the system checks—

633
00:33:45,070 --> 00:33:46,330
"Task accomplished,"

634
00:33:46,340 --> 00:33:47,730
and gives me a pill,

635
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:49,110
a miracle drug.

636
00:33:49,110 --> 00:33:50,310
I'd take it home, let Jiajia swallow it,

637
00:33:50,310 --> 00:33:51,370
and she'd be cured.

638
00:33:56,260 --> 00:33:57,070
Dr. Yang.

639
00:33:58,320 --> 00:33:59,160
Dr. Yang.

640
00:34:01,270 --> 00:34:02,000
Officer Hu.

641
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:02,680
Hu Wenjing.

642
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:03,140
Nice to meet you.

643
00:34:03,140 --> 00:34:04,340
Nice to meet you, too.

644
00:34:04,750 --> 00:34:05,350
I stood you up.

645
00:34:05,350 --> 00:34:05,960
I'm sorry.

646
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,200
I came to apologize in person,

647
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:08,000
to say hello properly.

648
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:08,730
You should.

649
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:10,800
No, no...

650
00:34:10,820 --> 00:34:11,929
I understand.

651
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,280
Your dad said you were busy.

652
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:13,920
Very busy.

653
00:34:14,110 --> 00:34:16,370
About the blind date—my dad agreed to it.

654
00:34:16,380 --> 00:34:17,670
I personally had no intention of it.

655
00:34:17,670 --> 00:34:19,530
I needed to make that clear to you.

656
00:34:22,030 --> 00:34:22,510
Still…

657
00:34:22,510 --> 00:34:23,670
I'm glad to meet you.

658
00:34:23,710 --> 00:34:24,429
Me too.

659
00:34:24,449 --> 00:34:25,380
Glad to meet you.

660
00:34:25,639 --> 00:34:26,969
Xinyu, I'll head up now.

661
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:30,949
He's...

662
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:32,750
You know him?

663
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:34,239
My classmate,

664
00:34:34,920 --> 00:34:35,550
Cheng Ken.

665
00:34:36,510 --> 00:34:37,280
Cheng Ken.

666
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:39,080
He's my friend's older brother.

667
00:34:39,620 --> 00:34:40,820
What happened to him?

668
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:43,800
His daughter has uremia,

669
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:44,880
on dialysis.

670
00:34:45,110 --> 00:34:46,510
He's going through a lot.

671
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,840
Please, go ahead with your work.

672
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:50,480
Goodbye.

673
00:34:52,719 --> 00:34:53,440
Goodbye.

674
00:35:54,460 --> 00:35:58,040
[How to Make Milk Tablets]

675
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:38,680
[High-Phosphorus Foods Prohibited]

676
00:37:05,630 --> 00:37:06,210
Xiaoyu.

677
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:08,300
Wake up. Time for breakfast.

678
00:37:11,990 --> 00:37:12,760
Get up.

679
00:37:17,030 --> 00:37:17,760
Jiajia.

680
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:18,170
Hurry,

681
00:37:18,170 --> 00:37:20,370
brush your teeth
and call Xiaoyu to eat.

682
00:37:22,030 --> 00:37:22,720
Xiaoyu.

683
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:24,070
Come out for breakfast.

684
00:37:56,510 --> 00:37:57,170
Fresh ones.

685
00:37:57,760 --> 00:38:00,150
Dad, you baked milk tablets again?

686
00:38:00,570 --> 00:38:02,300
Last batch is almost finished.

687
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,110
These are newly baked.

688
00:38:03,110 --> 00:38:04,840
Eat them with Xiaoyu.

689
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,030
Spoon.

690
00:38:10,190 --> 00:38:10,720
It's hot.

691
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:13,250
Put it down, put it down.

692
00:38:13,590 --> 00:38:14,630
Eat later.

693
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:15,340
No rush.

694
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,800
I have to work overtime tonight.

695
00:38:28,670 --> 00:38:30,320
I'll be home a little late.

696
00:38:31,760 --> 00:38:34,550
Dad, can I stay up later then?

697
00:38:35,550 --> 00:38:36,440
Why?

698
00:38:37,410 --> 00:38:38,400
When you come back,

699
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,430
Xiaoyu can come out.

700
00:38:40,590 --> 00:38:43,180
I want to watch cartoons
with her a bit longer.

701
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:47,720
Alright.

702
00:38:50,110 --> 00:38:52,040
Then I'll try to come back earlier.

703
00:38:58,480 --> 00:38:59,920
This burger tastes awful.

704
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:00,550
Tell me—

705
00:39:01,190 --> 00:39:03,850
Nuanfeng still doesn't
even have a McDonald's?

706
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:06,280
Your injury should be
almost healed by now, right?

707
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,430
Still lying around like that?

708
00:39:07,430 --> 00:39:08,750
Didn't you say you'd help me make money

709
00:39:08,750 --> 00:39:09,830
and take me abroad?

710
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:13,070
You've just been hanging around here
eating and doing nothing every day.

711
00:39:13,070 --> 00:39:15,470
When are you going
to fulfill your promise?

712
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:17,300
If you don't show some action soon,

713
00:39:17,300 --> 00:39:18,830
I'll report you right away.

714
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:21,280
Knowingly hiding a criminal,

715
00:39:21,280 --> 00:39:23,320
providing shelter

716
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:25,400
to help him evade legal punishment—

717
00:39:25,430 --> 00:39:27,100
that's the crime of harboring.

718
00:39:27,100 --> 00:39:28,840
If the circumstances
are especially serious,

719
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:31,290
it's 3 to 10 years in prison.

720
00:39:32,070 --> 00:39:32,800
Tell me.

721
00:39:33,270 --> 00:39:35,070
Harboring an armed drug dealer—

722
00:39:35,710 --> 00:39:37,240
does that count as serious?

723
00:39:44,890 --> 00:39:46,620
I never should've trusted you.

724
00:39:46,810 --> 00:39:48,020
You big liar.

725
00:39:51,030 --> 00:39:53,490
Big plans require patience and loneliness.

726
00:39:53,880 --> 00:39:55,620
I'm just conserving my strength,

727
00:39:55,620 --> 00:39:57,280
waiting for the storm to pass.

728
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:58,070
Besides,

729
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,000
during this time

730
00:40:00,050 --> 00:40:01,880
I helped you pay off over 400,000 in debt.

731
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:02,770
Still not satisfied?

732
00:40:02,770 --> 00:40:03,890
Over 400,000?

733
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:06,280
When my business was good,

734
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:08,140
I could make that back in 2 months.

735
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:10,310
I've been staying here
with you for over a month.

736
00:40:10,310 --> 00:40:11,970
How many pieces have you sold?

737
00:40:12,020 --> 00:40:14,550
Your fake bags and fake clothes
are practically growing mold.

738
00:40:14,550 --> 00:40:15,950
Anyone even buying them?

739
00:40:16,800 --> 00:40:18,930
Anyway, I took such a huge risk for you.

740
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:20,960
I'm not just letting this go.

741
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,250
Don't worry, Li Xiaoya.

742
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,510
I'm a man of my word.

743
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:29,040
I'll start working very soon.

744
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:29,770
But

745
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:32,160
you need to help me buy one more thing.

746
00:40:38,950 --> 00:40:40,810
Then I'll trust you one last time.

747
00:40:41,540 --> 00:40:42,230
Buy what?

748
00:40:43,510 --> 00:40:44,290
Milk tea.

749
00:40:46,590 --> 00:40:47,550
Milk tea?

750
00:40:49,630 --> 00:40:51,110
Are you out of your mind?

751
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:54,030
Sounds like you're just full
and craving something sweet.

752
00:40:54,030 --> 00:40:55,480
I've got a friend in Nuanfeng
called Daquan.

753
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:56,840
He used to run with me.

754
00:40:57,150 --> 00:40:59,680
Now he opened a milk tea shop
to distribute goods.

755
00:40:59,680 --> 00:41:01,400
Nuanfeng is his territory.

756
00:41:03,130 --> 00:41:04,530
I've thought it through.

757
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:07,170
With a narcotics officer dead,

758
00:41:07,190 --> 00:41:08,360
going back to Haizhou to make money again

759
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:09,590
is impossible now.

760
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:12,650
The best option is
to bring Daquan under our wing,

761
00:41:13,230 --> 00:41:15,960
use his sales network to make quick cash.

762
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:20,720
He used to follow you.

763
00:41:21,620 --> 00:41:23,020
Will he still listen now?

764
00:41:23,730 --> 00:41:24,530
If he listens,

765
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:27,820
I'll use the chicken to hatch the egg.

766
00:41:27,930 --> 00:41:28,730
If he doesn't,

767
00:41:30,460 --> 00:41:32,660
I'll kill the chicken and take the eggs.

768
00:41:46,130 --> 00:41:47,060
Why are you here?

769
00:41:47,740 --> 00:41:48,750
I came to see you.

770
00:41:49,230 --> 00:41:50,490
I don't want to see you.

771
00:41:50,690 --> 00:41:52,090
We're already divorced.

772
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:56,340
Even divorced people
can be friends, right?

773
00:41:56,470 --> 00:41:58,600
You haven't posted on Moments lately,

774
00:41:58,630 --> 00:41:59,630
haven't been selling anything—

775
00:41:59,630 --> 00:42:00,920
nothing happened, did it?

776
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:01,850
Cheng Xiaodong,

777
00:42:02,110 --> 00:42:03,840
do you not understand Chinese?

778
00:42:04,020 --> 00:42:06,550
We have nothing to do
with each other anymore.

779
00:42:07,550 --> 00:42:09,210
Have you paid off those debts?

780
00:42:10,040 --> 00:42:12,280
Have the creditors come
looking for you recently?

781
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:13,880
If you need help, just say it.

782
00:42:14,670 --> 00:42:15,960
I've told you already.

783
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:17,690
It was just cash-flow trouble.

784
00:42:17,850 --> 00:42:19,310
It's all settled long ago.

785
00:42:20,470 --> 00:42:21,400
Still, thank you

786
00:42:21,510 --> 00:42:22,640
for caring about me.

787
00:42:22,700 --> 00:42:24,250
Do you have another man now?

788
00:42:26,950 --> 00:42:28,480
What are you talking about?

789
00:42:28,510 --> 00:42:30,090
You've got another man, don't you?

790
00:42:30,090 --> 00:42:31,350
What's wrong with you?

791
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:32,960
Li Xiaoya.

792
00:42:33,550 --> 00:42:34,670
I can give you a good life.

793
00:42:34,670 --> 00:42:35,550
Trust me.

794
00:42:35,760 --> 00:42:37,360
What good life?

795
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:38,670
You don't even know
what a good life looks like.

796
00:42:38,670 --> 00:42:39,710
How would I not know?

797
00:42:39,710 --> 00:42:40,960
Don't you just love money

798
00:42:40,960 --> 00:42:42,000
and big-name brands?

799
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:42,840
Are you insane?

800
00:42:42,840 --> 00:42:43,440
All those Chanel,

801
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:44,360
LV and Hermès nonsense...

802
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:45,190
Li Xiaoya!

803
00:42:46,420 --> 00:42:47,220
Get in the car.

804
00:42:49,030 --> 00:42:49,840
So shallow.

805
00:42:52,160 --> 00:42:53,290
I'm so pissed off.

806
00:42:59,130 --> 00:43:00,170
So pissed off.

807
00:43:03,530 --> 00:43:04,530
Come on, you two

808
00:43:04,840 --> 00:43:06,070
are already broken up.

809
00:43:06,070 --> 00:43:07,590
Can you stop clinging like this?

810
00:43:07,590 --> 00:43:08,650
Right there on the street?

811
00:43:08,650 --> 00:43:10,600
If he keeps harassing you on his own,

812
00:43:10,600 --> 00:43:11,830
call the police or tell me.

813
00:43:11,830 --> 00:43:12,690
I'll handle it.

814
00:43:13,280 --> 00:43:14,150
When it really matters,

815
00:43:14,150 --> 00:43:15,360
I still gotta rely on my bestie.

816
00:43:15,360 --> 00:43:16,000
You, me, and Wang Ping —

817
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:17,320
it’s been almost a month
since the three of us

818
00:43:17,320 --> 00:43:18,250
last met, right?

819
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:19,840
I've been crazy busy lately.

820
00:43:19,840 --> 00:43:20,690
I really have.

821
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:21,580
Busy with what?

822
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:23,700
Still that same case from before?

823
00:43:23,870 --> 00:43:25,530
Did you catch the drug dealer?

824
00:43:25,760 --> 00:43:27,160
How could I tell you that?

825
00:43:27,650 --> 00:43:28,180
Alright.

826
00:43:28,220 --> 00:43:28,700
I get it.

827
00:43:28,730 --> 00:43:29,460
Discipline.

828
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:30,630
I won't ask.

829
00:43:30,850 --> 00:43:32,110
What are you busy with?

830
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:33,710
Me?

831
00:43:35,590 --> 00:43:36,960
I'm preparing to immigrate.

832
00:43:36,960 --> 00:43:38,630
Again? Immigration again?

833
00:43:39,230 --> 00:43:40,800
This time it's really solid.

834
00:43:40,800 --> 00:43:41,860
But once you leave,

835
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:43,590
we basically won't see each other anymore.

836
00:43:43,590 --> 00:43:45,150
I can video call you every day.

837
00:43:45,150 --> 00:43:46,480
I can report everything to you.

838
00:43:46,480 --> 00:43:47,740
Do I look that free?

839
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:48,670
Fine then.

840
00:43:48,750 --> 00:43:50,030
I'll video call Wang Ping instead—

841
00:43:50,030 --> 00:43:51,070
won't include you.

842
00:43:51,070 --> 00:43:51,980
Why are we splitting...

843
00:43:51,980 --> 00:43:52,940
Forming cliques?

844
00:43:52,940 --> 00:43:54,940
Three people split into two groups?

845
00:43:57,780 --> 00:43:58,450
You're

846
00:43:59,190 --> 00:44:00,230
telling me about this.

847
00:44:00,230 --> 00:44:01,030
Are you

848
00:44:01,240 --> 00:44:03,720
trying to give me a heads-up emotionally?

849
00:44:04,810 --> 00:44:07,340
Afraid I won't be able
to take it or something?

850
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:12,320
Your intuition

851
00:44:12,320 --> 00:44:13,670
is so sharp

852
00:44:13,920 --> 00:44:15,180
that it even scares me.

853
00:44:15,190 --> 00:44:16,070
Why are you scared of me?

854
00:44:16,070 --> 00:44:18,270
Only the bad guys should be scared of me.

855
00:44:24,160 --> 00:44:31,770
[Next Episode Preview]
